frameDefinitions: A speaker marks a Conceded_state_of_affairs as being or implying a contradiction to the Main_assertion.
The words in this frame describe the manipulation of an Entity by an Agent.
The Denoted_quantity is (generally) an imprecise characterization of the quantity of Individuals or a Mass, made with reference to a relatively easily and precisely imaginable Reference_quantity.
An Agent causes a Theme to move away from a location, the Source.
A Topical_entity has properties which are affected by the existence and association of an Entity.
An Owner has (or lacks) a Possession. ''
frameExamples: <t>Although</t> she had some trouble , she was able to finish about two hours early .
It took <t><fex name='Denoted_quantity'>about</fex></t> three hours, but we 're done now.
I saw that several men in dark suits had <t>removed</t> all of the evidence from the scene.
By the 1920s a characteristic book <t>had</t> black and white photographic illustrations only .
The river's part of my  manor, but of course it also <t>belongs</t> to the River Police.
listRoleDefinitions: A proposition or set of propositions that the speaker wants the addressee to believe or take for granted. This statement is not asserted, but presupposed by the speaker of the sentence, and is mentioned to contrast with the <fen>Main_assertion</fen>. It would or could seem to predict a situation different than the <fen>Main_assertion</fen>, but, for reasons left implicit, this normal prediction is contradicted by the fact that the <fen>Main_assertion</fen> and the <fen>Conceded_state_of_affairs</fen> are both simultaneously true.
An entity which metonymically stands in for an associated <fen>Statement</fen>.

The statement that the speaker wishes to assert or offer as their main contribution to the discourse, which is be modified or hedged in some way by the <fen>Conceded_state_of_affairs</fen>. The force of the contribution of the <fen>Main_assertion</fen> is presented as undiluted by the fact that something different from the <fen>Main_assertion</fen> would normally by predicted, based on the facts in the <fen>Conceded_state_of_affairs</fen>.

The <fen>Agent</fen> manipulates an object. <fen>Agent</fen> typically refers to animate beings, but is also extended to mechanical and other inanimate objects.  <fen>Agent</fen> is most frequently expressed as the external argument of verbs:
The <fen>Entity</fen> being manipulated often occurs as the direct object of verbs:

The part of the <fen>Agent</fen>'s body being used to manipulate the <fen>Entity</fen> may also be expressed. While the default is for an <fen>Agent</fen> to use his/her hands, other body parts may be specified. This frame element usually occurs as a PP-complement.
When the manipulation takes place
The spatial setting in which the manipulation takes place.
The quantity denoted by phrases headed by the Target.
A substance that is being quantified.
A collection of entities, either quantifiable physical beings (e.g. <m>toads</m>) or quantifiable units whether physical or not (e.g. <m>dollars</m>).
A relatively precise quantity in some oft-used form that is used as the basis for defining the <fen>Denoted_quantity</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
Theme is the object that changes location.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the initial location of the <fen>Theme</fen>, before it changes location.
The non-Agentive cause of the removing event.
The time at which the removal takes place.
The location where the removal takes place.
Some entity, abstract or concrete, which is stated to exist and be associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>.
The entity under discussion, whose states and properties are impacted by its association with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> exists and is associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>
The place where the <fen>Entity</fen> is associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>.
The entity that owns a posession.

The thing which is owned by the Owner.
Ex.:  I <t>have</t> <fex name='Possession'>twenty bucks</fex>.
(This does not include bodyparts or medical conditions, but does include intellectual property, etc.)
This role indicates the <fen>Time</fen> interval during which the <fen>Owner</fen> has a possession.
